ThinkPart(
    type='think',
    think='Let me now start writing all the backend files. I\'ll create them one
by one.\n\nFor the matching service, I\'ll need to:\n1. Use ioredis for caching\
n2. Use DataSource for transactions and raw queries\n3. Handle Haversine distanc
e calculation\n4. Implement composite scoring\n\nLet me think about the raw SQL 
query for recommendations. I need to be careful with the SQL to make it work cor
rectly.\n\n```sql\nSELECT \n  u.id as user_id,\n  up.nickname,\n  up.bio,\n  up.
avatar_url,\n  TIMESTAMPDIFF(YEAR, up.birth_date, CURDATE()) as age,\n  6371 * A
COS(\n    COS(RADIANS(:lat)) * COS(RADIANS(up.latitude)) * COS(RADIANS(up.longit
ude) - RADIANS(:lng))\n    + SIN(RADIANS(:lat)) * SIN(RADIANS(up.latitude))\n  )
as distance,\n  -- score components\n  (1 - LEAST(6371 * ACOS(...), :maxDist) / 
:maxDist) * 0.5 as distance_score,\n  CASE \n    WHEN u.last_login_at >= DATE_SU
B(NOW(), INTERVAL 1 DAY) THEN 0.3\n    WHEN u.last_login_at >= DATE_SUB(NOW(), I
NTERVAL 7 DAY) THEN 0.21\n    WHEN u.last_login_at >= DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 3
0 DAY) THEN 0.12\n    ELSE 0.03\n  END as activity_score,\n  CASE WHEN u.created
_at >= DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 7 DAY) THEN 0.2 ELSE 0 END as new_user_score\nFR
OM users u\nJOIN user_profiles up ON u.id = up.user_id\nWHERE up.is_complete = 1
\n  AND u.id != :userId\n  AND up.latitude IS NOT NULL\n  AND up.longitude IS NO
T NULL\n  AND (:preferredGender = \'both\' OR up.gender = :preferredGender)\n  A
ND (up.preferred_gender IS NULL OR up.preferred_gender = \'both\' OR up.preferre
d_gender = :myGender)\n  AND 6371 * ACOS(...) <= :maxDistance\n  AND u.id NOT IN
(\n    SELECT target_id FROM match_actions WHERE actor_id = :userId\n    UNION\n
   SELECT actor_id FROM match_actions WHERE target_id = :userId AND action = \'p
ass\'\n    UNION\n    SELECT user_a_id FROM matches WHERE user_b_id = :userId AN
D status != \'unmatched\'\n    UNION\n    SELECT user_b_id FROM matches WHERE us
er_a_id = :userId AND status != \'unmatched\'\n    UNION\n    SELECT blocked_id 
FROM blocks WHERE blocker_id = :userId\n    UNION\n    SELECT blocker_id FROM bl
ocks WHERE blocked_id = :userId\n  )\nORDER BY (distance_score + activity_score 
+ new_user_score) DESC\nLIMIT :limit\n```\n\nWait, the PRD says:\n- "当前用户性
别符合目标用户的 preferred_gender" - this means if target\'s preferred_gender is
\'both\', anyone matches. If it\'s \'male\', only males match.\n- "目标用户性别
符合当前用户的 preferred_gender" - same logic\n\nFor the distance calculation in
score:\n- `score += (1 - distance / max_distance) * 0.5`\n\nFor activity:\n- 24h
内 1.0 -> 0.3 * 1.0 = 0.3\n- 7天内 0.7 -> 0.3 * 0.7 = 0.21\n- 30天内 0.4 -> 0.3 
* 0.4 = 0.12\n- 其余 0.1 -> 0.3 * 0.1 = 0.03\n\nFor new user:\n- 注册7天内加 0.2
\n\nSo the total score = distance_component + activity_component + new_user_bonu
s\n= (1 - distance/max_distance) * 0.5 + activity_weight * activity_multiplier +
new_user_bonus\n\nLet me now write the actual code. I\'ll create the files.',
    encrypted=None
)
